@page "/"

<PageTitle>Blazor Cache Demo</PageTitle>

<h1>Welcome to Blazor Cache Demo</h1>

<p>
    This sample application demonstrates how to use the local storage cache service in Blazor.
</p>

<p>
    Navigate to the <a href="/cache-demo">Cache Demo</a> page to see the cache in action.
</p>

<h2>Key Features</h2>

<ul>
    <li>Automatic or manual expiration of cached items</li>
    <li>Background cleanup of expired items</li>
    <li>Cache metrics and statistics</li>
    <li>Type-safe storage and retrieval</li>
    <li>Full control over cache configuration</li>
</ul>

<h2>How to Use</h2>

<p>
    Inject the <code>ICacheService</code> interface into your components:
</p>

<pre>
    @("@inject ICacheService CacheService")
</pre>

<p>
    Then use the service methods to store, retrieve, and manage cached data:
</p>

<pre>
// Store data with custom expiration time
await CacheService.SetAsync("myKey", myData, TimeSpan.FromMinutes(30));

// Retrieve data
var data = await CacheService.GetAsync&lt;MyType&gt;("myKey");

// Check if a key exists
if (await CacheService.ExistsAsync("myKey"))
{
    // Do something
}

// Remove a specific item
await CacheService.RemoveAsync("myKey");

// Clear the entire cache
await CacheService.ClearAsync();
</pre>

<p>
    Go to the demo page to see these features in action.
</p>